Package: liondown
Title: An updated R Markdown thesis template using the bookdown package, adapted from Chester Ismay's thesisdown
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Callum", "Arnold", email = "cal.rk.arnold@gmail.com", role = "aut"),
    person("Chester", "Ismay", email = "chester.ismay@gmail.com", role = c("cre", "aut")),
    person("Nick", "Solomon", email = "nick@nicksolomon.me", role = "aut"))
Description: Using the bookdown package and LaTeX and Word thesis templates from
    Penn State University, this package aims to encourage reproducible research using
    simple Markdown syntax while embedding all of the R code to produce plots
    and analyses as well.
Maintainer: Callum Arnold <cal.rk.arnold@gmail.com>
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.0)
Imports: 
    dplyr,
    ggplot2,
    bookdown,
    knitr,
    here,
    R.utils
Suggests:
    remotes,
    usethis
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
SystemRequirements: pandoc (>= 1.18) - https://pandoc.org
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
